The paper discusses the use of AI and dialog system technologies for Intelligent Virtual Assistants, which falls under the category of natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The focus is on audio-visual scene-aware dialog, which involves analyzing visual and audio features, making it relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also explores attention mechanisms, which is a common topic in machine learning and deep learning (cs.SD). Finally, the paper discusses multimodal attention, which involves analyzing multiple modalities, making it relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
